pnpc-dam-collapse-in-laos-flee-deteriorating-relocation-centers','','','2020-06-30 07:52:09','2020-06-30 10:52:09','',0,'http://localhost/?p=21',0,'post','',0),(22,1,'2020-06-26 15:32:07','2020-06-26 18:32:07','','post-3','','inherit','open','closed','','post-3','','','2020-06-26 15:32:07','2020-06-26 18:32:07','',21,'http://localhost/wp-content/uploads/2020/06/post-3.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(23,1,'2020-06-26 15:32:14','2020-06-26 18:32:14','','Survivors of PNPC Dam Collapse in Laos Flee Deteriorating Relocation Centers','','inherit','closed','closed','','21-revision-v1','','','2020-06-26 15:32:14','2020-06-26 18:32:14','',21,'http://localhost/index.php/2020/06/26/21-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(24,1,'2020-06-26 15:33:27','2020-06-26 18:33:27','','Committee votes to ban harmful pesticides from June 1','','publish','open','open','','committee-votes-to-ban-harmful-pesticides-from-june-1','','','2020-06-30 07:51:12','2020-06-30 10:51:12','',0,'http://localhost/?p=24',0,'post','',0),(25,1,'2020-06-26 15:32:50','2020-06-26 18:32:50','','post-4','','inherit','open','closed','','post-4','','','2020-06-26 15:32:50','2020-06-26 18:32:50','',24,'http://localhost/wp-content/uploads/2020/06/post-4.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(26,1,'2020-06-26 15:33:27','2020-06-26 18:33:27','','Committee votes to ban harmful pesticides from June 1','','inherit','closed','closed','','24-revision-v1','','','2020-06-26 15:33:27','2020-06-26 18:33:27','',24,'http://localhost/index.php/2020/06/26/24-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(27,2,'2020-06-26 15:34:02','2020-06-26 18:34:02','<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Southeast Asia is one of the biggest sources of plastic waste from land to the ocean, and Thailand is among the top five contributors. In January, Thailand placed a ban on single-use plastic, and was looking to reduce its plastic waste by 30% this year.&nbsp;&nbsp;</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>But the COVID-19 pandemic and the resulting lockdown has led to a huge rise in the country\'s plastic waste. According to the Thailand Environment Institute (TEI), the average amount of plastic waste went from 2,120 tons per day in 2019 to approximately 3,440 tons per day between January and April 2020. The rise in the month of April alone was nearly 62%.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":1} -->\n<h1>Texto em H1</h1>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading -->\n<h2>Texto em H2</h2>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":3} -->\n<h3>Texto em H3</h3>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":4} -->\n<h4>Texto em H4</h4>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Texto em P</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":5} -->\n<h5>Texto em H5</h5>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":6} -->\n<h6>Texto em H6</h6>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->','Huge rise in single-use plastic during Thailand’s lockdown','','publish','open','open','','huge-rise-in-single-use-plastic-during-thailands-lockdown','','','2020-06-30 08:09:15','2020-06-30 11:09:15','',0,'http://localhost/?p=27',0,'post','',0),(28,1,'2020-06-26 15:33:57','2020-06-26 18:33:57','Descrição da imagem aqui podendo ser do tamanho de uma frase curta','post-5','','inherit','open','closed','','post-5','','','2020-06-26 16:35:13','2020-06-26 19:35:13','',27,'http://localhost/wp-content/uploads/2020/06/post-5.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(29,1,'2020-06-26 15:34:02','2020-06-26 18:34:02','','Huge rise in single-use plastic during Thailand’s lockdown','','inherit','closed','closed','','27-revision-v1','','','2020-06-26 15:34:02','2020-06-26 18:34:02','',27,'http://localhost/index.php/2020/06/26/27-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(30,1,'2020-06-26 15:39:27','2020-06-26 18:39:27','<!-- wp:newspack-blocks/homepage-articles {\"className\":\"is-style-default\",\"showExcerpt\":false,\"showAuthor\":false,\"showAvatar\":false,\"postLayout\":\"grid\",\"columns\":2,\"postsToShow\":2,\"typeScale\":3} /--