urating news, commentary and resources on development, its environmental and social impacts, and the context affecting the Mekong Region</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:shortcode -->\n[mc4wp_form id=\"65\"]\n<!-- /wp:shortcode --></div>\n<!-- /wp:column -->\n\n<!-- wp:column {\"width\":33.33} -->\n<div class=\"wp-block-column\" style=\"flex-basis:33.33%\"><!-- wp:columns -->\n<div class=\"wp-block-columns\"><!-- wp:column -->\n<div class=\"wp-block-column\"><!-- wp:paragraph {\"textColor\":\"secondary\"} -->\n<p class=\"has-text-color has-secondary-color\"><strong>LATEST EDITION</strong></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph --></div>\n<!-- /wp:column -->\n\n<!-- wp:column -->\n<div class=\"wp-block-column\"><!-- wp:paragraph {\"align\":\"right\",\"textColor\":\"primary-variation\"} -->\n<p class=\"has-text-color has-text-align-right has-primary-variation-color\"><strong>No: 263</strong></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph --></div>\n<!-- /wp:column --></div>\n<!-- /wp:columns -->\n\n<!-- wp:image {\"id\":73,\"sizeSlug\":\"large\"} -->\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img src=\"http://localhost/wp-content/uploads/2020/06/mkeye-6-768x432-1.jpg\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-73\"/></figure>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph {\"textColor\":\"secondary\"} -->\n<p class=\"has-text-color has-secondary-color\"><strong>Título do conteúdo que geralmente será um nome grande</strong></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph --></div>\n<!-- /wp:column --></div>\n<!-- /wp:columns --></div></div>\n<!-- /wp:cover -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->','Homepage','','inherit','closed','closed','','7-revision-v1','','','2020-06-29 12:14:49','2020-06-29 15:14:49','',7,'http://localhost/index.php/2020/06/29/7-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(77,1,'2020-06-29 12:56:05','2020-06-29 15:56:05','<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Seis meses depois de o mundo registrar oficialmente o primeiro caso da Covid-19, o surto ganha a cada dia mais força. Dados publicados neste domingo pela OMS revelam um número inédito de novos casos em 24 horas. No período avaliado pela entidade, foram 189 mil casos extras, com o Brasil liderando as infecções e mortes. Nesta semana, a agência mundial da Saúde vai marcar os seis meses do primeiro caso informado à entidade, em 31 de dezembro de 2019. Mas a marca será usada para que a cúpula da OMS alerte, nesta segunda-feira, que não há sinais de que a crise esteja perdendo força. Um apelo será lançado a partir de Genebra para que governos assumam suas responsabilidades</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->','Brasil lidera e covid-19 registra novo recorde no mundo em 24 horas','','publish','open','open','','brasil-lidera-e-covid-19-registra-novo-recorde-no-mundo-em-24-horas','','','2020-06-30 11:04:55','2020-06-30 14:04:55','',0,'http://localhost/?p=77',0,'post','',0),(78,1,'2020-06-29 12:55:51','2020-06-29 15:55:51','','','','inherit','open','closed','','covid','','','2020-06-30 11:03:28','2020-06-30 14:03:28','',77,'http://localhost/wp-content/uploads/2020/06/covid.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(79,1,'2020-06-29 12:56:05','2020-06-29 15:56:05','<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Seis meses depois de o mundo registrar oficialmente o primeiro caso da Covid-19, o surto ganha a cada dia mais força. Dados publicados neste domingo pela OMS revelam um número inédito de novos casos em 24 horas. No período avaliado pela entidade, foram 189 mil casos extras, com o Brasil liderando as infecções e mortes. Nesta semana, a agência mundial da Saúde vai marcar os seis meses do primeiro caso informado à entidade, em 31 de dezembro de 2019. Mas a marca será usada para que a cúpula da OMS alerte, nesta segunda-feira, que não há sinais de que a crise esteja perdendo força. Um apelo será lançado a partir de Genebra para que governos assumam suas responsabilidades</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->','Brasil lidera e covid-19 registra novo recorde no mundo em 24 horas','','inherit','closed','closed','','77-revision-v1','','','2020-06-29 12:56:05','2020-06-29 15:56:05','',77,'http://localhost/index.php/2020/06/29/77-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(80,1,'2020-06-29 12:58:32','2020-06-29 15:58:32','<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>A&nbsp;<a href=\"https://g1.globo.com/tudo-sobre/ans/\">Agência Nacional de Saúde Suplementar</a>&nbsp;(ANS) incluiu nesta segunda-feira (29) o teste sorológico para o novo coronavírus na lista de coberturas obrigatórias dos planos de saúde. A medida foi publicada hoje no Diário Oficial da União e passa a valer imediatamente.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>A inclusão do teste teste sorológico no Rol de Procedimentos e Eventos em Saúde atende à decisão judicial dada em Ação Civil Pública e pode ser feito sem custo extra, contando que haja requisição feita por um médico.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>A mudança era ensaiada desde março pelo Ministério da Saúde. Naquela ocasião, o então secretário-executivo do Ministério da Saúde, João Gabbardo dos Reis, disse que&nbsp;<a href=\"https://g1.globo.com/bemestar/coronavirus/noticia/2020/03/10/teste-para-coronavirus-sera-incluido-na-lista-de-cobertura-obrigatoria-dos-planos-de-saude.ghtml\">os planos poderiam cobrar pelo teste pois o procedimento não estava no rol de cobertura obrigatória</a>, mas que as empresas seriam obrigadas a bancar os testes.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->','ANS define teste sorológico para o novo coronavírus como cobertura obrigatória de planos de saúde','','publish','open','open','','ans-define-teste-sorologico-para-o-novo-coronavirus-como-cobertura-obrigatoria-de-planos-de-saude','','','2020-06-30 11:05:42','2020-06-30 14:05:42','',0,'http://localhost/?p=80',0,'post','',0),(81,1,'2020-06-29 12:58:14','2020-06-29 15:58:14','','','','inherit','open','closed','','sangue','','','2020-06-30 11:05:03','2020-06-30 14:05:03','',80,'http://localhost/wp-content/uploads/2020/06/sangue.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(82,1,'2020-06-29 12:58:32','2020-06-29 15:58:32','<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>A&nbsp;<a href=\"https://g1.globo.com/tudo-sobre/ans/\">Agência Nacional de Saúde Suplementar</a>&nbsp;(ANS) incluiu nesta segunda-feira (29) o teste sorológico para o novo coronavírus na lista de coberturas obrigatórias dos planos de saúde. A medida foi publicada hoje no Diário Oficial da União e passa a valer imediatamente.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>A inclusão do teste teste sorológico no Rol de Procedimentos e Eventos em Saúde atende à decisão judicial dada em Ação Civil Pública e pode ser feito sem custo extra, contando que haja requisição feita por um médico.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>A mudança era ensaiada desde março pelo Ministério da Saúde. Naquela ocasião, o então secretário-executivo do Ministério da Saúde, João Gabbardo dos Reis, disse que&nbsp;<a href=\"https://g1.globo.com/bemestar/coronavirus/noticia/2020/03/10/teste-para-coronavirus-sera-incluido-na-lista-de-cobertura-obrigatoria-dos-planos-de-saude.ghtml\">os planos poderiam cobrar pelo teste pois o procedimento não estava no rol de cobertura obrigatória</a>, mas que as empresas seriam obrigadas a bancar os testes.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->','ANS define teste sorológico para o novo coronavírus como cobertura obrigatória de planos de saúde','','inherit','closed','closed','','80-revision-v1','','','2020-06-29 12:58:32','2020-06-29 15:58:32','',80,'http://localhost/index.php/2020/06/29/80-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(83,1,'2020-06-29 13:00:09','2020-06-29 16:00:09','<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Manifestantes ocupam nesta segunda-feira (29) duas faixas da avenida Afonso Pena, no Centro de Belo Horizonte, para protestar contra o fechamento do comércio. O encontro começou às 10h na porta da prefeitura da capital.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Entre as reivindicações estão a reabertura de bares, restaurantes, academias e shoppings. A Polícia Militar e a Empresa de Transporte e Trânsito de Belo Horizonte (BHTrans) estão no local monitorando o trânsito.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->','Manifestantes pedem reabertura do comércio em Belo Horizonte','','publish','open','open','','manifestantes-pedem-reabertura-do-comercio-em-belo-horizonte','','','2020-06-30 11:06:37','2020-06-30 14:06:37','',0,'http://localhost/?p=83',0,'post','',0),(84,1,'2020-06-29 12:59:44','2020-06-29 15:59:44','','','','inherit','open','closed','','caixao-em-protesto','','','2020-06-30 11:05:44','2020-06-30 14:05:44','',83,'http://localhost/wp-content/uploads/2020/06/caixao-em-protesto.jpeg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(85,1,'2020-06-29 13:00:09','2020-06-29 16:00:09','<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Manifestantes ocupam nesta segunda-feira (29) duas faixas da avenida Afonso Pena, no Centro de Belo Horizonte, para protestar contra o fechamento do comércio. O encontro começou às 10h na porta da prefeitura da capital.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Entre as reivindicações estão a reabertura de bares, restaurantes, academias e shoppings. A Polícia Militar e a Empresa de Transporte e Trânsito de Belo Horizonte (BHTrans) estão no local monitorando o trânsito.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->','Manifestantes pedem reabertura do comércio em Belo Horizonte','','inherit','closed','closed','','83-revision-v1','','','2020-06-29 13:00:09','2020-06-29 16:00:09','',83,'http://localhost/index.php/2020/06/29/83-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(86,1,'2020-06-29 13:00:23','0000-00-00 00:00:00','','Rascunho automático','','auto-draft','open','open','','','','','2020-06-29 13:00:23','0000-00-00 00:00:00','',0,'http://localhost/?p=86',0,'post','',0),(87,1,'2020-06-29 13:02:05','2020-06-29 16:02:05','<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>“It fully reflects the active engagement of Cambodia in the MLC and demonstrates that the China-Cambodia cooperation within the MLC is highly fruitful. We hope the projects will help improve Cambodian people’s livelihoods and speed up Cambodia’s development in economy, society and other areas,” he said.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>“The application of 2021 project is now under way. We expect an early confirmation of a new round of quality projects, which will provide more support for economic and social development of the region after the COVID-19 pandemic. China would like to work with Cambodia as well as other Lancang-Mekong River countries to implement the MLC Special Fund Projects,” Mr Wang added.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Mr Sokhonn said that in February last year, Cambodia implemented the second batch of projects supported by the MLC Special Fund 2018.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>“Since the launch of the MLC Special Fund in 2016, these projects have contributed to enhancing the socio-economic development of the Mekong-Lancang countries through narrowing development gaps, deepening mutual understanding and trust and strengthening our capacity to better respond to the needs of our peoples,” he said.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->','Cambodia the biggest beneficiary of MLC Special Fund projects','','publish','open','open','','cambodia-the-biggest-beneficiary-of-mlc-special-fund-projects','','','2020-06-29 13:03:14','2020-06-29 16:03:14','',0,'http://localhost/?p=87',0,'post','',0),(88,1,'2020-06-29 13:01:47','2020-06-29 16:01:47','','','','inherit','open','closed','','4342','','','2020-06-30 11:12:05','2020-06-30 14:12:05','',87,'http://localhost/wp-content/uploads/2020/06/4342.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(89,1,'2020-06-29 13:02:05','2020-06-29 16:02:05','<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>“It fully reflects the active engagement of Cambodia in the MLC and demonstrates that the China-Cambodia cooperation within the MLC is highly fruitful. We hope the projects will help improve Cambodian people’s livelihoods and speed up Cambodia’s development in economy, society and other areas,” he said.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>“The application of 2021 project is now under way. We expect an early confirmation of a new round of quality projects, which will provide more support for economic and social development of the region after the COVID-19 pandemic. China would like to work with Cambodia as well as other Lancang-Mekong River countries to implement the MLC Special Fund Projects,” Mr Wang added.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Mr Sokhonn said that in February last year, Cambodia implemented the second batch of projects supported by the MLC Special Fund 2018.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>“Since the launch of the MLC Special Fund in 2016, these projects have contributed to enhancing the socio-economic development of the Mekong-Lancang countries through narrowing development gaps, deepening mutual understanding and trust and strengthening our capacity to better respond to the needs of our peoples,” he said.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->','Cambodia the biggest beneficiary of MLC Special Fund projects','','inherit','closed','closed','','87-revision-v1','','','2020-06-29 13:02:05','2020-06-29 16:02:05','',87,'http://localhost/index.php/2020/06/29/87-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(90,1,'2020-06-29 13:02:50','2020-06-29 16:02:50','<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>If the findings of a new study are to be believed, the novel coronavirus holding the world hostage at the moment poses a greater threat to the health of humans, animals and plants than previously suspected. The study – which still awaits peer-review –&nbsp;<a href=\"https://www.news-medical.net/news/20200622/Dire-warning-on-contamination-of-water-and-COVID-19-spread.aspx\">suggests</a>&nbsp;that Covid-19 is able to remain stable in contaminated water for up to 25 days, and places a special focus on contamination through sewage.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Even though these findings still need final verification, they nonetheless bring attention to the potentially great risk for infection from dirty water at a time when personal hygiene is of the essence. The sewage systems in Southeast Asia’s urban centers are often inadequate, with wastewater being pumped into rivers and the ocean, where diseases can potentially become endemic within flora and fauna and thus, when consumed, act as a new vector for the coronavirus to affect human health.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->','Dirty flow: The Covid-19 risk in Southeast Asia’s rivers','','publish','open','open','','dirty-flow-the-covid-19-risk-in-southeast-asias-rivers','','','2020-06-30 11:09:51','2020-06-30 14:09:51','',0,'http://localhost/?p=90',0,'post','',0),(91,1,'2020-06-29 13:02:46','2020-06-29 16:02:46','','4951944214_b111404211_k','','inherit','open','closed','','4951944214_b111404211_k','','','2020-06-29 13:02:46','2020-06-29 16:02:46','',90,'http://localhost/wp-content/uploads/2020/06/4951944214_b111404211_k.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(92,1,'2020-06-29 13:02:50','2020-06-29 16:02:50','<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>If the findings of a new study are to be believed, the novel coronavirus holding the world hostage at the moment poses a greater threat to the health of humans, animals and plants than previously suspected. The study – which still awaits peer-review –&nbsp;<a href=\"https://www.news-medical.net/news/20200622/Dire-warning-on-contamination-of-water-and-COVID-19-spread.aspx\">suggests</a>&nbsp;that Covid-19 is able to remain stable in contaminated water for up to 25 days, and places a special focus on contamination through sewage.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Even though these findings still need final verification, they nonetheless bring attention to the potentially great risk for infection from dirty water at a time when personal hygiene is of the essence. The sewage systems in Southeast Asia’s urban centers are often inadequate, with wastewater being pumped into rivers and the ocean, where diseases can potentially become endemic within flora and fauna and thus, when consumed, act as a new vector for the coronavirus to affect human health.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->','Dirty flow: The Covid-19 risk in Southeast Asia’s rivers','','inherit','closed','closed','','90-revision-v1','','','2020-06-29 13:02:50','2020-06-29 16:02:50','',90,'http://localhost/index.php/2020/06/29/90-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(94,1,'2020-06-29 13:15:04','2020-06-29 16:15:04','<!-- wp:newspack-blocks/homepage-articles {\"className\":\"is-style-default\",\"showExcerpt\":false,\"showAuthor\":false,\"showAvatar\":false,\"postLayout\":\"grid\",\"columns\":2,\"postsToShow\":2,\"categories\":[\"3\"],\"typeScale\":3} /-->\n\n<!-- wp:newspack-blocks/homepage-articles {\"showAuthor\":false,\"postLayout\":\"grid\",\"categories\":[\"3\"],\"typeScale\":3} /-->\n\n<!-- wp:cover {\"customOverlayColor\":\"#cdde87\",\"className\":\"home__newsletter-bkg\"} -->\n<div class=\"wp-block-cover has-background-dim home__newsletter-bkg\" style=\"background-color:#cdde87\"><div class=\"wp-block-cover__inner-container\"><!-- wp:columns -->\n<div class=\"wp-block-columns\"><!-- wp:column {\"width\":66.66} -->\n<div class=\"wp-block-column\" style=\"flex-basis:66.66%\"><!-- wp:html -->\n<i class=\"far fa-newspaper home__newsletter-icon\"></i>\n<!-- /wp:html -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"textColor\":\"primary\"} -->\n<h2 class=\"has-primary-color has-text-color\">WEEKLY NEWS DIGEST</h2>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph {\"customTextColor\":\"#333333\"} -->\n<p style=\"color:#333333\" class=\"has-text-color\">Curating news, commentary and resources on development, its environmental and social impacts, and the context affecting the Mekong Region</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:shortcode -->\n[mc4wp_form id=\"65\"]\n<!-- /wp:shortcode --></div>\n<!-- /wp:column -->\n\n<!-- wp:column {\"width\":33.33} -->\n<div class=\"wp-block-column\" style=\"flex-basi